    <title>Google is inserting search links into webpages in the Google App now</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Image of the Google “G” logo on a blue, black, and purple background." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kcNWxLNanMuUNn5XUzUJjz0T_4s=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73747335/STK093_Google_03.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Illustration: The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="dDYKBP"&gt;The Google App for iOS can automatically convert some website text into links to Google Search results, as announced in a community post that &lt;a href="https://www.seroundtable.com/google-ios-app-page-annotation-38451.html"&gt;&lt;em&gt;SERoundtable&lt;/em&gt; spotted&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="oBlaPh"&gt;Google &lt;a href="https://support.google.com/websearch/thread/308719098/page-annotation-in-google-app-browser-for-ios?hl=en"&gt;calls the feature&lt;/a&gt; “Page Annotations” and says it “extracts interesting entities from the webpage and highlights them in line,” which can then take you out to Search results when you tap them — inserting links without explicitly asking the user or the site owner first. It seems like a curious move for a company embroiled in antitrust fights over both its &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24300617/doj-google-search-antitrust-chrome-breakup"&gt;search&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24237832/google-monopoly-trial-ad-tech-antitrust-us-search"&gt;advertising&lt;/a&gt; businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class="e-image"&gt;
        
      &lt;cite&gt;Image: Google&lt;/cite&gt;
      &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;A screenshot shows what the links, er, “Page Annotations” look like.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p id="y6z08K"&gt;Google &lt;a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1h9I0TbN-H_1e85CqXYb1ng7rQfg2ijfODc1sBxPBd08/viewform?edit_requested=true"&gt;has a form&lt;/a&gt; for web publishers to opt out of the links. According to...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/25/24305922/google-app-ios-inserting-search-links-websites"&gt;Continue reading&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

</content>
