    <title>Meta’s mixed-reality attempt at a Wii Sports knockoff is coming</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A picture of a person wearing an orange longsleeve shirt, jeans, and a Quest headset, swinging a virtual bowling ball toward a floating image of a bowling alley." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Hj_cZMLbWb6z3jRnRgen0iJ_bu0=/113x0:1328x810/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73747141/Home_Sports.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Home Sports &lt;em&gt;remembers that bowling was the best part of &lt;/em&gt;Wii Sports. | Image: Meta&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="mVuGG5"&gt;A new game called &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meta.com%2Fexperiences%2Fhome-sports%2F8975028309180826%2F&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F11%2F25%2F24305847%2Fmeta-quest-home-sports-vr-mr-tennis-bowling-hockey-game" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Home Sports&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is coming to the Meta Quest 3 and 3S &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meta.com%2Fblog%2Fquest%2Fhome-sports-wishlist%2F&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F11%2F25%2F24305847%2Fmeta-quest-home-sports-vr-mr-tennis-bowling-hockey-game" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;on December 11th&lt;/a&gt;, and from its aesthetic to its music, this $19.99 title is clearly trying to be the &lt;em&gt;Wii Sports&lt;/em&gt; (or &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/27/23044617/nintendo-switch-sports-wii-sports-party-game"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nintendo Switch Sports&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; if you like) for mixed reality. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class="e-image"&gt;
        
      &lt;cite&gt;Images: Meta / Nintendo&lt;/cite&gt;
      &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;That logo looks very familiar.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="IMtA2X"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Nintendo Music now has Wii Sports tunes.","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/12/24294447/nintendo-music-now-has-wii-sports-tunes"},{"title":"The strange and surprisingly intense world of Wii Sports speedrunners","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2019/8/5/20750161/wii-sports-speedrunning-nintendo"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="Dcm4rT"&gt;Like Nintendo’s simplistic motion control-based sports series, &lt;em&gt;Home Sports&lt;/em&gt; offers several games: hockey, badminton, pickleball, mini-golf, and bowling. It’s playable solo and multiplayer, where your Meta avatar represents you in a match. Meta says the game can adapt to your play space, but it also uses the Quest boundaryless mode for those with access to wide-open spaces. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="WZTCa2"&gt;A blatant knockoff of Nintendo’s &lt;em&gt;Sports &lt;/em&gt;series&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;it...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/25/24305847/meta-quest-home-sports-vr-mr-tennis-bowling-hockey-game"&gt;Continue reading&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

</content>
