    <title>Anthropic launches tool to connect AI systems directly to datasets</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Vector illustration of the Anthropic logo." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tHPAbCKvAG-4O7y1wwwS2k_pMeU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73747087/STK269_ANTHROPIC_C.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="ADEAO7"&gt;Anthropic has released a new open-source tool to connect AI assistants directly to the information they need to inform their responses or carry out tasks. &lt;a href="https://www.anthropic.com/news/model-context-protocol"&gt;The new Model Context Protocol&lt;/a&gt; (MCP) provides a universal connection to all sorts of data sources, which Anthropic says will improve performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="2MnmUU"&gt;Earlier this month, OpenAI started testing a new “Work with Apps” feature that &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296745/chatgpts-mac-app-will-be-able-to-read-your-code#:~:text=%2D%20The%20Verge&amp;amp;text=Emma%20Roth-,ChatGPT's%20Mac%20app%20will%20be%20able%20to%20read%20your%20code,paste%20it%20into%20the%20app."&gt;lets the Mac version of ChatGPT directly connect&lt;/a&gt; to certain coding apps. Anthropic’s tool, on the other hand, aims to work across all AI systems and data sources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="V1OrOE"&gt;&lt;a href="https://x.com/alexalbert__/status/1861079886619918644"&gt;As noted by Alex Albert&lt;/a&gt;, Anthropic’s head of Claude relations, developers currently have to create custom code for each dataset they want their AI model to draw from. With Anthropic’s MCP, Albert says...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
